  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nForge, Cast, Anvil, Foundryup\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nfoundryup\n\n### Operating System\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nFoundryup should ensure that there are no running processes current before downloading and updating the binaries on a users OS.\r\n\r\ne.g.\r\n```console\r\nanvil :~ $ anvil 0.1.0 (f817db3 2022-08-16T00:04:34.491624Z)\r\nusr :~ $ foundryup\r\nfoundryup: installing foundry (version nightly, tag nightly-f817db31ab97a62fa635237da424c0e7105ce489)\r\nfoundryup: downloading latest forge, cast and anvil\r\n############################################################################################################################################################################### 100.0%\r\nfoundryup: downloading manpages\r\n############################################################################################################################################################################### 100.0%\r\nfoundryup: installed - forge 0.2.0 (f817db3 2022-08-16T00:04:34.401357Z)\r\nfoundryup: installed - cast 0.2.0 (f817db3 2022-08-16T00:04:34.401357Z)\r\nfoundryup: installed - anvil 0.1.0 (f817db3 2022-08-16T00:04:34.491624Z)\r\nfoundryup: done\r\n\r\nusr :~ $ anvil\r\nthread 'main' panicked at 'error binding to 127.0.0.1:8545: error creating server listener: Address already in use (os error 48)', /Users/runner/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/hyper-0.14.18/src/server/server.rs:87:17\r\nnote: run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable to display a backtrace\r\nAbort trap: 6\r\nusr :~ $ # ....\r\nanvil :~ $ anvil 0.1.0 (e385736 2022-08-13T00:04:28.532461Z)\r\n```",
